Taiwan’s CPC Seeks to Buy West African Sweet Crude Oil for May

-- B y   Y u - h u a y   S u n
-- 
2011-03-22T09:08:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-22/taiwan-s-cpc-seeks-to-buy-west-african-sweet-crude-oil-for-may.html
CPC Corp.,  Taiwan ’s state oil
refiner, is seeking to buy low-sulfur, West African crude for
loading in May, the company said in a  notice  on its website.  Details of the refiner’s planned purchase are as follows:  Low-sulfur, or sweet crude oil, has less than 0.5 percent
sulfur by weight. The oil is more expensive than so-called sour
crude oil, which contains more than 0.5 percent sulfur.  To contact the reporter on the story:
Yu-huay Sun in Taipei at 
